Package org.chronos.chronodb.internal.impl.query.parser.token

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    QueryToken
    A QueryToken represents a single, lexicographic element in a sequence that defines a ChronoDBQuery.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AndToken
    An AndToken represents a binary relation between two query expressions using the BinaryQueryOperator.AND.
    BeginToken
    A BeginToken is used in conjunction with an EndToken to form matching braces for precedence handling in a ChronoDBQuery.
    EndOfInputToken
    An EndOfInputToken marks the end of the input in an QueryTokenStream.
    EndToken
    A EndToken is used in conjunction with an BeginToken to form matching braces for precedence handling in a ChronoDBQuery.
    KeyspaceToken
    A KeyspaceToken is usually the first token in a QueryTokenStream.
    NotToken
    A NotToken negates the result of the subsequent query statements.
    OrToken
    An AndToken represents a binary relation between two query expressions using the BinaryQueryOperator.OR.
    WhereToken
    A WhereToken specifies an atomic filter.
